'''Luca Zinedine Zidane''' ({{langx|ar|لوكا زين الدين زيدان}}; born 13 May 1998) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Segunda División]] club [[Granada CF|Granada]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]].

Zidane began his career with [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] before competing professionally in [[Spain]], mainly in Segunda División with [[Racing Santander]], [[Rayo Vallecano]], [[SD Eibar|Eibar]] and currently [[Granada CF|Granada]].

He represented his country of birth, France at youth international levels. Having qualified through his paternal grandparents, he was selected for the Algeria senior national team in 2025, and played for them at the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]]. He is the son of French professional [[Manager (association football)|football manager]] and former player [[Zinedine Zidane]].

==Early life==
Luca Zinedine Zidane was born in [[Aix-en-Provence]], France, on 13 May 1998. He is the son of the footballer [[Zinedine Zidane]] and professional dancer Veronique Fernández.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49133535|title=Maldini, Zidane, Kluivert, Hagi, Weah – the sons of legends making their own way|date=27 July 2019|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> He is the second of four brothers, all of who – [[Enzo Zidane|Enzo]], [[Théo Zidane|Théo]], and [[Elyaz Zidane|Elyaz]] – are professional footballers who developed at the [[La Fábrica (Real Madrid)|Real Madrid youth academy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/bleus-apres-enzo-voila-luca-zidane-588871.html|title=Bleus – Après Enzo, voilà Luca Zidane !|first=RMC|last=SPORT|date=17 March 2014 |publisher=}}</ref> Zidane is of [[Spaniards|Spanish descent]] through his mother,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.femmeactuelle.fr/bio/veronique-zidane-2019687|title=Actualités Véronique Zidane|publisher=}}</ref> and of Algerian [[Arab-Berber|Arab Berber]] descent through his father.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lebuteur.com/interview/detail?titre=zidane-a-coeur-ouvert-2e-partie-jattends-que-lalgerie-passe-au-deuxieme-tour-et-meme-plus&id=41|title=Interview: Zidane à cœur ouvert (2e partie) : "J'attends que l'Algérie passe au deuxième tour et même plus !"|last=Kreo|website=lebuteur.com}}</ref> He has French and Algerian nationality.<ref>{{Cite web |last=S |first=Zakaria |date=11 January 2023 |title=Quand le fils de Zidane affiche son ambition de représenter l'Algérie |url=https://www.algerie360.com/quand-le-fils-de-zidane-affiche-son-ambition-de-representer-lalgerie/ |access-date=27 December 2023 |website=www.algerie360.com |language=fr}}</ref>

==Club career==
Zidane joined the [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] [[Real Madrid CF (youth)|youth academy]] at the age of 6 in 2004 and plays as a goalkeeper.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2016/09/09/57d2cc4122601dd9448b45c4.html|title=Zidane's four sons joined Real when he was at the club – MARCA English|date=9 September 2016 |publisher=}}</ref> He worked his way up from the academy, eventually joining [[Real Madrid Castilla|Castilla]], the [[reserve team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.footmercato.net/liga/real-madrid-luca-zidane-poursuit-son-ascension_152269|title=Real Madrid : Luca Zidane poursuit son ascension|date=20 April 2015 |publisher=}}</ref>

===Real Madrid===
Zidane's father, Zinedine Zidane, joined the Real Madrid coaching staff in 2014, thereby becoming Luca's manager at various levels early in his footballing career.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2018/05/19/5b006defe5fdead4738b45a0.html|title=LaLiga – Real Madrid: Luca Zidane selected by his father|date=19 May 2018|work=Marca}}</ref> Zidane made his professional debut for Real Madrid in their last league game of the 2017–18 season: a 2–2 [[La Liga]] tie with [[Villarreal CF]] on 19 May 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2018/05/19/spain/primera-division/villarreal-club-de-futbol/real-madrid-club-de-futbol/2529619/|title=Villarreal vs. Real Madrid – 19 May 2018|publisher=Soccerway}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2018/05/19/5b00945ce5fdead8738b45d6.html|title=LaLiga – Villarreal 2–2 Real Madrid: Luca Zidane: When I play I'm Luca, not Zidane|last1=Calderón|first1=J.L.|last2=French|first2=Oliver|date=19 May 2018|work=Marca}}</ref>

====Loan to Santander====
Zidane was loaned to [[Racing de Santander|Racing Santander]] of [[Segunda División]] on 8 July 2019 for the 2019–20 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realracingclub.es/noticia/luca-zidane-jugara-en-el-racing-la-campana-201920-cedido-por-el-real-madrid|title=Luca Zidane jugará en el Racing la campaña 2019/20 cedido por el Real Madrid|date=8 July 2019|work=realracingclub.es}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2019/07/official-announcement-luca-zidane|title=Official Announcement: Luca Zidane|date=8 July 2019|work=realmadrid.com}}</ref> He made his debut on 17 August 2019 in a 1–0 home loss to [[Málaga CF|Málaga]], in which he suffered an injury to the muscle on the back of his right leg.<ref>{{cite news |title=Luca Zidane se lesiona en el primer partido de la temporada |trans-title=Luca Zidane gets injured in the first game of the season|url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/segunda-division/luca-zidane-lesionado-primer-partido-7600185 |accessdate=24 August 2019 |work=Sport |date=20 August 2019 |language=Spanish}}</ref>

===Rayo Vallecano===
On 5 October 2020, Zidane joined [[Rayo Vallecano]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Luca Zidane nuevo jugador del Rayo Vallecano|url=http://www.rayovallecano.es/noticia/luca-zidane-nuevo-jugador-del-rayo-vallecano|accessdate=5 October 2020|work=rayovallecano.es|date=5 October 2020|language=es}}</ref> He made his debut on 2 December, coming as substitute for [[Stole Dimitrievski]] who was sent off in a 1–0 loss to [[CD Leganés|Leganés]]. When Dimitrievski played in [[UEFA Euro 2020]] for [[North Macedonia national football team|North Macedonia]], he played in all the remaining games of the season and led the team to promotion to the top flight after defeating [[Girona FC|Girona]] in the play-off final.<ref>{{cite news |title=Luca Zidane: "No hay palabras para describir este momento"|trans-title=Luca Zidane: "There are no words to describe this moment"|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/20210620/410120841660/luca-zidane-no-hay-palabras-para-describir-este-momento.html |access-date=3 October 2021 |work=[[Mundo Deportivo]] |date=20 June 2021 |language=Spanish}}</ref>

===Eibar===
On 1 September 2022, [[free agent]] Zidane signed a two-year contract with [[SD Eibar|Eibar]] in the second division.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sdeibar.com/noticia/luca-zidane-decimo-fichaje-del-eibar|title=Luca Zidane, décimo fichaje del Eibar|trans-title=Luca Zidane, tenth signing of Eibar|publisher=SD Eibar|language=es|date=1 September 2022|accessdate=2 September 2022}}</ref> On 22 March of the following year, he renewed his link with the club until 2026.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/eibar/2023/03/22/641ad626e2704e9a1c8b4574.html|title=El Eibar renueva a Luca Zidane hasta 2026|trans-title=Eibar renew Luca Zidane until 2026|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=22 March 2023|accessdate=5 July 2024}}</ref>

===Granada===
On 5 July 2024, Zidane agreed to a three-year deal with [[Granada CF|Granada]], [[2023–24 La Liga|recently relegated to the second division]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.granadacf.es/noticias/comunicado-oficial-or-luca-zidane-nuevo-jugador-del-granada-cf|title=Comunicado Oficial {{!}} Luca Zidane, nuevo jugador del Granada CF|trans-title=Official announcement {{!}} Luca Zidane, new player of Granada CF|publisher=Granada CF|language=es|date=5 July 2024|accessdate=5 July 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in France to French-born parents of Algerian and Spanish descent, Zidane represented France at youth international level. He was part of the [[France national under-17 football team|France under-17 squad]] that won the [[2015 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]] and also featured at the [[2015 FIFA U-17 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/u17worldcup/news/y=2015/m=9/news=luca-zidane-i-don-t-want-to-be-compared-to-my-father-2676306.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150910162815/http://www.fifa.com/u17worldcup/news/y=2015/m=9/news=luca-zidane-i-don-t-want-to-be-compared-to-my-father-2676306.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=10 September 2015|title=Luca Zidane: I don't want to be compared to my father|publisher=FIFA.com|date=8 September 2015}}</ref> He made one appearance for the [[France national under-20 football team|under-20 team]] on 23 March 2018 in a 1–0 friendly defeat to the [[United States men's national under-20 soccer team|United States]] in Spain.<ref>{{cite news |title=U.S. U-20 MNT nets late-game winner to defeat France U-21 <!--recorded as U20 game on FFF website, error in title--> [''sic''] squad |url=https://www.soccerwire.com/news/u-s-u-20-mnt-nets-late-game-winner-to-defeat-france-u-21-squad/ |accessdate=20 November 2019 |publisher=Soccerwire |date=27 March 2018}}</ref>

On 19 September 2025, FIFA approved Zidane's request to change his sporting nationality from French to Algerian, making him eligible to play for the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]].<ref name=ALG>{{cite web|url=https://www.faf.dz/equipe-nationale-luca-zinedine-zidane-change-sa-nationalite-sportive/|title=Équipe nationale : Luca Zinedine Zidane change sa nationalité sportive|trans-title=National team: Luca Zinedine Zidane changes his sporting nationality|language=French|publisher=[[Algerian Football Federation]]|date=19 September 2025}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cp3v7dex01no|title=Son of France legend Zidane switches allegiance to Algeria|date=19 September 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> On 2 October 2025, he accepted their call-up for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – CAF Group G|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches against [[Somalia national football team|Somalia]] and [[Uganda national football team|Uganda]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.faf.dz/eliminatoires-du-mondial-2026-la-liste-de-petkovic-pour-les-matchs-face-a-la-somalie-et-a-louganda/|title=Éliminatoires du Mondial 2026 : la liste de Petkovic pour les matchs face à la Somalie et à l'Ouganda|trans-title=2026 World Cup qualifiers: Petkovic's squad list for the matches against Somalia and Uganda|language=French|publisher=[[Algerian Football Federation]]|date=2 October 2025}}</ref> His debut with Algeria came twelve days later in the 2026 FIFA World Cup qualification match against Uganda after being named in the starting line-up.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ca.sports.yahoo.com/news/world-cup-2026-qualifiers-algeria-092000675.html |title=World Cup 2026 qualifiers / Algeria 2 - Uganda 1: Zidane reacts! |publisher=Yahoo Sports |date=15 October 2025 }}</ref>

Zidane was named in manager [[Vladimir Petković]]'s Algeria national team for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]] in [[Morocco]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://xscore808.com/luca-zidane-named-in-algeria-squad-for-afcon-2025/ |title=Luca Zidane Named in Algeria Squad for AFCON 2025 |publisher=Xscores |date=14 December 2025 }}</ref>

<ref>{{cite news |title=Luca Zidane heroics guide Algeria to shock win over Netherlands |url=https://footballscore808.com/luca-zidane-heroics-guide-algeria-to-shock-win-over-netherlands/ |access-date=2026-06-04 |work=Footballscore808 |date=2026-06-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20260604052116/https://footballscore808.com/luca-zidane-heroics-guide-algeria-to-shock-win-over-netherlands/ |archive-date=2026-06-04 |url-status=live}}</ref>

